# Workspace context

Working directory: `/Users/YOUR_USERNAME/workspace`

---

## Google Workspace — use `gws` CLI

You have full access to Gmail, Drive, Calendar, and Sheets via the `gws` CLI.
Run it with the shell tool. Auth is already set up — no login needed.

### Gmail

```bash
# List recent unread threads
gws gmail users threads list --params '{"userId":"me","maxResults":20,"q":"is:unread"}'

# Get a full thread
gws gmail users threads get --params '{"userId":"me","id":"THREAD_ID","format":"full"}'

# Search emails
gws gmail users messages list --params '{"userId":"me","q":"from:boss@company.com"}'
```

**Decoding email bodies** (base64url-encoded):
```bash
echo "BASE64URL_STRING" | python3 -c "import sys,base64; print(base64.urlsafe_b64decode(sys.stdin.read().strip()+'==').decode('utf-8','ignore'))"
```

### Google Drive

```bash
# List files
gws drive files list --params '{"pageSize":20,"fields":"files(id,name,mimeType,modifiedTime)"}'

# Export a Google Doc as plain text
gws drive files export --params '{"fileId":"FILE_ID","mimeType":"text/plain"}' --output /tmp/doc.txt
```

### Google Calendar

```bash
# Upcoming events
gws calendar events list --params '{"calendarId":"primary","maxResults":10,"orderBy":"startTime","singleEvents":true,"timeMin":"'$(date -u +%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ)'"}'
```

### Sheets

```bash
# Read values
gws sheets spreadsheets values get --params '{"spreadsheetId":"SHEET_ID","range":"Sheet1!A1:Z100"}'
```

---

## Tips

- Use `--page-all` on list commands to fetch all pages
- Always confirm before sending emails or deleting calendar events
